main event: A witness observed two orange-white lights in the sky over Watchung, New Jersey, on April 30, 1961, which appeared to move toward and then away from them.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 15 seconds,The lights were observed under slightly hazy weather conditions,Witness reliability is noted as reliable,The report implies that the objects might have been an aircraft,There were no photographs included in the report.
sighted object: two orange-white lights in the sky
witness description: Reliable witness reported seeing the lights.
